Good "old school" fun

LayoutNode.Content: I got this for my little cousin, who loves Barbies. While I didn't play with Barbies myself when Iwas younger, it's nice to see toys from my childhood still being enjoyed by the youth of today(you know, when they're not on their iPads). Most of the time I see her, she's playing Minecraftor some other mobile game, so it's refreshing to see her play with actual tangible toys like I didwhen I was younger. That it contends with her electronic devices speaks for itself in theentertainment value of this set. I will say on the downside, the pieces are small and she'salready lost a few pieces. I also feel like maybe it should have come with at least one Barbiecharacter rather than having to buy one separately. Otherwise, it seems to be good wholesomefun for my cousin. I received this product at a discounted price in return for my unbiasedreview. See more

I wish this set would come with a doll to make ita complete gift set for girls who may not have any barbie yet. And although every girl lovespink, I wish the colors should be more pastel. Other than that, this is still a great addition to mynieces' collection. I am happy with the purchase and received it at a discounted price for myunbiased review. See more
